medium; text-wrap: wrap; background-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><span style=\"outline: 0px; text-size-adjust: none; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 14px;\">对于加密货币现货投资者来说，通过TCEHK合约交易，他们只需少量投资，就可以轻松地在短期内对冲自己的资产。 只有这样，才能在波动的市场中锁定风险，更好地把握获利机会。</span></p><p style=\"outline: 0px; text-size-adjust: none; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(99, 112, 133); font-family: proxima-nova, sans-serif; font-size: medium; text-wrap: wrap; background-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><br/></p><p style=\"outline: 0px; text-size-adjust: none; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(99, 112, 133); font-family: proxima-nova, sans-serif; font-size: medium; text-wrap: wrap; background-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><span style=\"outline: 0px; text-size-adjust: none; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 14px;\">此外，TCEHK为客户提供多种杠杆比例以满足用户从稳定到激进的各种交易风格。 特别是高杠杆与低门槛交易方式相结合，提高了交易的时间效率，从而增加了交易的娱乐性。</span></p><p style=\"outline: 0px; text-size-adjust: none; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(99, 112, 133); font-family: proxima-nova, sans-serif; font-size: medium; text-wrap: wrap; background-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><br/></p><p style=\"outline: 0px; text-size-adjust: none; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(99, 112, 133); font-family: proxima-nova, sans-serif; font-size: medium; text-wrap: wrap; background-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><span style=\"outline: 0px; text-size-adjust: none; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 14px;\">以TCEHK为代表的一站式金融平台。 就像信息技术、互联网、人工智能等各种跨代技术创新一样，早期伴随新技术而来的巨大泡沫在第一个十年后突然破灭。 随着泡沫的破灭，行业的稳固发展，产业机会的真正出现，TCEHK也在此时应运而生。 TCEHK致力于成为全球领先的一站式综合金融服务商。 为用户提供一个更容易跨过金融投资门槛的工具，让更广泛的人群可以直接接触杠杆交易和期权交易，为众多领域提供更易获取的综合金融方向。 为以后修行领域的大爆发，培植土壤和基石！</span></p><p><span style=\"outline: 0px; text-size-adjust: none; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 14px;\"></span><br/></p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p>',0,1591113600,1699247274,'/images/zwtp.png','/images/zwtp.png',1),(88,6,'en','Trading guide',0,0,0,0,'管理员',0,'Trading guide','Aiccoin','<p>1，问：什么是区块链？</p><p><br/></p><p>答：区块链是一种去中心化的、点对点传输、安全可信的数据库。</p><p><br/></p><p>2，问：什么是比特币？</p><p><br/></p><p>答：比特币是全球第一种去中心化的货币。</p><p><br/></p><p>3，问：区块链和比特币是什么关系？</p><p><br/></p><p>答：比特币是区块链的第一个应用，区块链技术是比特币的底层技术。</p><p><br/></p><p>4，问：比特币是怎么发行的？</p><p><br/></p><p>答：比特币是没有特定的发行机构，依靠一套去中心化的发行机制，逐步将比特币发行出去的（系统自动生成BTC作为奖励，激励矿工参与记账）。</p><p><br/></p><p>5，问：比特币怎么转账？</p><p><br/></p><p>答：在比特币交易平台、钱包、客户端输入比特币地址、接收方地址、转账金额和转账手续费，确认支付后交易信息会在比特币网络中全网广播，矿工每隔10分钟会将未被记账的交易打包进一个区块，完成一次确认，通常需要经过6次确认，确保交易记录没有被篡改，交易才算真正完成。</p><p><br/></p><p>6，问：比特币和Q币有什么不同？</p><p><br/></p><p>答：比特币是一种去中心化的数字资产，没有发行主体。Q币是靠腾讯的信用背书发行的电子货币（电子积分），其实不是货币，Q币需要中心化的发行机构。</p><p><br/></p><p>7，问：比特币转账要付多少手续费？</p><p><br/></p><p>答：转账手续费一般为0.001-0.0015个比特币，多付手续费可以被更快记账哦。</p><p><br/></p><p>8，问：比特币和USDT地址是什么？</p><p><br/></p><p>答：是一串由字母和数字组成的，26-34字符串，比特币和USDT地址就是个人的比特币和USDT账户，相当于你的银行卡号，任何人都可以通过你的比特币地址给你转账比特币和USDT，可以下载一个比特币和USDT钱包或者在交易平台上注册。</p><p><br/></p><p>9，问：比特币节点是什么？什么是全节点？</p><p><br/></p><p>答：比特币是一种点对点的电子现金系统，更直接地说是节点对节点，每笔交易由发起方向周围的节点进行广播，扩散至全网，每个比特币钱包都是一个节点。拥有完整区块链账本的节点叫做全节点，负责比特币交易的广播和验证，挖矿的节点验证该交易正确后会记录至区块链账本。</p><p><br/></p><p>10，问：比特币的数字签名是什么？</p><p><br/></p><p>答：只有比特币转账的转出方生成的一段防伪造的字符串。通过验证该字符串，一方面证明交易是转出方本人发起的，另一方面证明交易信息在传输中没有被更改。</p><p><br/></p><p>11，问：什么是矿工？矿工主要工作是什么？</p><p><br/></p><p>答：矿工相当于记账员，主要工作是交易确认，数据打包。</p><p><br/></p><p>12，问：量化交易是什么？</p><p><br/></p><p>答：就是自动化交易。以先进的数学模型替代人为的主观判断，避免投资者做出非理性的投资决策。包括跨平台搬砖、趋势交易，对冲等。</p><p><br/></p><p>13，问：什么是跨平台搬砖？</p><p><br/></p><p>答：当不同目标平台价差达到一定金额，价高平台卖出、价低的平台买入。</p><p><br/></p><p>14，问：什么是对冲？</p><p><br/></p><p>答：同时进行两笔与行情相关、买卖方向相反、数量相当、盈亏相抵的交易。</p><p><br/></p><p>15，问：什么是去中心化交易平台？</p><p><br/></p><p>答：不用注册账户，使用个人数字资产账户即可参与交易，每笔交易都通过区块链进行，需等待区块链确认才算交易成功。平台不负责保管客户的资产和私钥等，避免交易平台的道德风险，要千万保管好自己的私钥。</p><p><br/></p><p>16，问：币币交易是什么？</p><p><br/></p><p>答：就是一种加密货币兑换另一种加密货币，不同币种按照各自时时的价格进行交易。</p><p><br/></p><p>17，问：什么是钱包？</p><p><br/></p><p>答：存储和使用数字货币的工具。包括比特币地址（类似于银行卡账号）和私钥（类似于银行卡密码），核心功能就是保护客户的私钥。</p><p><br/></p><p>18，问：比特币钱包的种类有哪些？</p><p><br/></p><p>答：PC钱包、手机钱包、网页钱包、脑钱包和纸钱包。</p><p><br/></p><p>19，问：比特币钱包按照私钥的存储方式分为几种？</p><p><br/></p><p>答：冷钱包，网络不能访问到你私钥的钱包，避免黑客盗取私钥的风险，相对于安全。热钱包，互联网能够访问到你私钥的钱包，是在线钱包，转账效率高，但不那么安全。</p><p><br/></p><p>20，问：全节点钱包、轻钱包和中心化钱包是什么？</p><p><br/></p><p>答：全节点钱包是核心钱包，需要同步区块链上所有数据，占用内存较大，可以完全实现去中心化。轻钱包：对数据进行分析后，仅同步并存储与自身相关的数据，运行时依赖于比特币网络上的其他全节点（Bither/Electrum）。中心化钱包：不依赖比特币网络，所有数据均从自己的中心化服务器获得。（交易效率很高，可以实时到账）交易平台注册的就是中心化钱包。</p><p><br/></p><p>21，问：区块链记录哪些信息？</p><p><br/></p><p>答：区块头（每个区块中前80个字节）、交易详情（详细记载了每笔交易的转出方、收入方、金额及转出方的数字签名，是每个区块的主要内容）、交易计数器（表述每个区块中包含交易的数量）、区块大小（表示每个区块数据的大小）。</p><p><br/></p><p>22，问：区块链按准入机制分为哪几类？</p><p><br/></p><p>答：公有链：公开透明，任何个体或者团体都可以在公有链上发送交易，交易能够获得有效确认，每个人都有竞争记账权；</p><p><br/></p><p>私有链：完全封闭，仅采用区块链技术进行记账，记账权不公开，只记录内部的交易，由公司或个人独享；</p><p><br/></p><p>联盟链：半公开，群体或组织内部使用的，需要预先指定几个节点为记账人，每个区块生成由预选记账人共同决定，其他节点可以交易，但没有记账权。</p><p><br/></p><p>23，问：区块链有哪些特性？</p><p><br/></p><p>答：去中心化、不可篡改、共识机制、分布式数据存储、点对点交易。</p><p><br/></p><p>24，问：区块链技术原理是什么？</p><p><br/></p><p>答：共识机制，保证每笔交易在所有记账节点上的一致性，让全网达成共识。</p><p><br/></p><p>25，问：区块链项目分为几类？</p><p><br/></p><p>答：币类、平台类、应用类、资产代币化。</p><p><br/></p><p>26，问：区块链的缺点有哪些？</p><p><br/></p><p>答：无隐私性、安全性问题、数据确认延迟性、监管等。</p><p><br/></p><p>27，问：什么是去中心化？</p><p><br/></p><p>答：在整个网络中没有中心化的硬件或者管理机构，任意节点的权利和义务都是均等的，且任意节点损坏或者失去都不会影响整个系统的运作。</p><p><br/></p><p>28，问：什么是挖矿？</p><p><br/></p><p>答：将一段时间内比特币系统中发生的交易进行确认，并记录在区块链上形成新区块的过程。</p><p><br/></p><p>29，问：什么是数字货币？</p><p><br/></p><p>答：数字货币相当于虚拟币=计算机密码学+分布式P2P网络+经济学+社会学的产物。</p><p><br/></p><p>30，问：什么是第三方钱包？</p><p><br/></p><p>答：是通过第三方介入支付的（只提供支付平台，不提供储存数据），例如通常用的IMTOKEN钱包。</p><p><br/></p><p>31，问：区块链主要应用在哪里？</p><p><br/></p><p>答：数字货币、泛金融应用（跨境支付、数字票据、征信管理、资产证券化、供应链金融、保险业务）、区块链 + 行业应用（区块链 + 医疗、区块链 + 物联网、区块链 + IP版权&amp;文化娱乐、区块链 + 公共服务&amp;教育）。</p><p><br/></p><p>32，问：什么是交易对？</p><p><br/></p><p>答：交易对是由2种不同的数字货币构成的，当你拥有交易对中的其中一种数字货币时，就可以通过这个交易对来交易另外一种数字货币。</p><p><br/></p><p>33，问：什么是市价交易？</p><p><br/></p><p>答：即不设定买入/卖出价格，可以保证及时成交，只需输入想买入的总数量即可。市价交易就是现在市场上是什么价格，你就直接以什么价格购买就叫做市价购买。</p><p><br/></p><p>34，问：什么是限价交易？</p><p><br/></p><p>答：限价交易即挂单交易，您可以自己设定买入价格，等市场价格波动到您设定的价格时即可成交。比如说你想买1枚比特币，你看到当前的报价是10000元，这个时候你觉得有点高，你想在9900元时买 入， 你就可以直接挂一个9900元的购买订单，如果有人以这个价格卖出，那么你这笔购买订单就交易成功了。这个时候你就获得1枚比特币到你的账户了。</p><p><br/></p><p>35，问：常见的币种有哪些？</p><p><br/></p><p>答：常见币种：BTC（比特币）ETH（以太坊）XRP（瑞波币）BCH（比特现金）LTC（莱特币）ADA（艾达币）XLM（恒星币）NEO（小蚁）XMR（门罗币）DASH（达世币）ETC（以太经典）USDT（泰达币）QTUM（量子链）EOS（柚子）TRX（波场）BNB（币安币）ZEC（大零币）。</p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p>1. Q: what is blockchain?</p><p><br/></p><p>A: blockchain is a decentralized, point-to-point, secure and trusted database.</p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p>2. Q: what is bitcoin?</p><p><br/></p><p>A: bitcoin is the world&#39;s first decentralized currency.</p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p>3. Q: what is the relationship between blockchain and bitcoin?</p><p><br/></p><p>A: bitcoin is the first application of blockchain, and blockchain technology is the underlying technology of bitcoin.</p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p>4. Q: how was bitcoin issued?</p><p><br/></p><p>A: bitcoin is gradually issued without specific issuing institutions, relying on a set of decentralized issuing mechanism (the system automatically generates BTC as a reward to encourage miners to participate in bookkeeping).</p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p>5. Q: how to transfer bitcoin?</p><p><br/></p><p>A: in currency trading platform, wallet, client input COINS address, recipient address, transfer amount and transfer fees, after confirm the payment will be in the currency of trade information network in the entire network broadcasting, miners every 10 minutes will not be trading account into a block, to complete a confirmation, usually takes 6 times to confirm, to ensure that trade record has not been tampered with, trading in order to be truly complete.</p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p>6. Q: what&#39;s the difference between bitcoin and Q coin?</p><p><br/></p><p>A: bitcoin is a decentralized digital asset with no issuer. Q coin is an electronic currency (electronic points) issued by tencent credit endorsement. Actually, it is not a currency. Q coin needs a centralized issuing institution.</p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p>7. Q: how much does bitcoin transfer cost?</p><p><br/></p><p>A: the transfer fee is generally 0.001-0.0015 bitcoins, and paying more can be credited faster.</p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p>8. Q: what are the addresses of bitcoin and USDT?</p><p><br/></p><p>A: it is a string of letters and Numbers, 26-34 strings, bitcoin and USDT address is a personal bitcoin and USDT account, equivalent to your bank card number, anyone can transfer bitcoin and USDT to you through your bitcoin address, you can download a bitcoin and USDT wallet or register on the trading platform.</p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p>9. Q: what is a bitcoin node? What is a full node?</p><p><br/></p><p>A: bitcoin is a point-to-point electronic cash system, or more directly, a node-to-node, where each transaction is broadcast from the originator to the surrounding nodes and spread across the network, with each bitcoin wallet being a node. The node with the complete blockchain account is called the full node, which is responsible for broadcasting and verifying bitcoin transactions. The mining node will record the correct transaction to the blockchain account.</p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p>10. Q: what is the digital signature of bitcoin?</p><p><br/></p><p>A: only a forgery proof string generated by the transferor of a bitcoin transfer. By verifying this string, you can either prove that the transaction was initiated by the sender himself or that the transaction information was not changed in transit.</p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p>11. Q: what is a miner? What is a miner&#39;s main job?</p><p><br/></p><p>A: miners work as bookkeepers, confirming trades and packaging data.</p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p>12. Q: what is quantitative trading?</p><p><br/></p><p>A: automated trading. Replace human subjective judgment with advanced mathematical model to avoid investors to make irrational investment decisions. This includes moving bricks across platforms, trend trading, hedging, etc.</p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p>13. Q: what is moving bricks across platforms?</p><p><br/></p><p>A: when different target platform difference achieves certain amount, the platform with high price is sold, low price is bought.</p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p>14. Q: what is hedging?</p><p><br/></p><p>A: two parallel, market-related, opposite, equal, break-even transactions.</p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p>15. Q: what is a decentralized trading platform?</p><p><br/></p><p>A: you don&#39;t need to register an account, you can use your personal digital asset account to participate in the transaction. Every transaction is conducted through the block chain, and the transaction is considered successful only after the confirmation of the block chain. The platform is not responsible for keeping the client&#39;s assets and private keys, so as to avoid the moral hazard of the trading platform.</p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p>16.Q: what is a coin trade?</p><p><br/></p><p>A: it&#39;s about exchanging one cryptocurrency for another, and trading in different currencies at their current prices.</p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p>17. Q: what is a wallet?</p><p><br/></p><p>A: tools for storing and using digital money. These include a bitcoin address (similar to a bank account number) and a private key (similar to a bank card password), the core function of which is to protect the customer&#39;s private key.</p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p>18. Q: what are the types of bitcoin wallets?</p><p><br/></p><p>A: PC wallet, mobile wallet, web wallet, brain wallet and paper wallet.</p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p>19. Q: how many bitcoin wallets are stored according to the private key?</p><p><br/></p><p>A: cold wallet, the network can not access your private key wallet, to avoid the risk of hackers stealing the private key, relatively safe. Hot wallet, a wallet that the Internet can access to your private key, is an online wallet that transfers money efficiently but securely.</p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p>20.Q: what are all-node wallets, light wallets and centralized wallets?</p><p><br/></p><p>A: the all-node wallet is the core wallet, which needs to synchronize all data on the blockchain, occupies a large memory, and can be completely decentralized. Light wallet: after analyzing the data, only synchronizes and stores the data related to itself, and the runtime relies on other all-nodes on the bitcoin network (Bither/Electrum). Centralised wallet: all data is obtained from its own centralised server, independent of the bitcoin network. (the transaction efficiency is very high, which can be delivered to the account in real time.) the transaction platform registered is the centralized wallet.</p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p>21. Q: what information does blockchain record?</p><p><br/></p><p>A: block head (each block of the top 80 bytes), transaction details (detailing the roll-out of the party, income party every transaction, amount and roll-out of digital signature, is the main content of each block), trading counter (the number of each block contains transactions), block size (the size of each block of data).</p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p>22. Q: what are the categories of blockchain according to the access mechanism?</p><p><br/></p><p>A: public chain: open and transparent, any individual or group can send transactions on the public chain, transactions can get effective confirmation, everyone has the right to compete bookkeeping;</p><p><br/></p><p>Private chain: completely closed, only using block chain technology for bookkeeping, bookkeeping rights are not public, only recording internal transactions, by the company or individual exclusive;</p><p><br/></p><p>Alliance chain: semi-public, group or internal use of the organization, need to designate several nodes in advance as bookkeepers, each block generated by pre-selected bookkeepers jointly decided, other nodes can trade, but no accounting rights.</p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p>23. Q: what are the features of blockchain?</p><p><br/></p><p>A: decentralized, tamper-proof, consensual, distributed data storage, peer-to-peer trading.</p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p>24. Q: what is the principle of blockchain technology?</p><p><br/></p><p>A: the consensus mechanism guarantees the consistency of every transaction at all accounting nodes, so that the whole network can reach a consensus.</p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p>25. Q: what are the categories of blockchain projects?</p><p><br/></p><p>A: currency, platform, application, and asset token.</p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p>26. Q: what are the disadvantages of blockchain?</p><p><br/></p><p>A: no privacy, security issues, data confirmation delay, supervision, etc.</p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p>27. Q: what is decentralization?</p><p><br/></p><p>A: there is no centralized hardware or management organization in the whole network, and the rights and obligations of any node are equal, and the damage or loss of any node will not affect the operation of the whole system.</p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p>28. Q: what is mining?</p><p><br/></p><p>A: confirm the transactions that take place in the bitcoin system over a period of time and record the process of forming new blocks on the blockchain.</p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p>29. Q: what is digital currency?</p><p><br/></p><p>A: digital currency is the product of virtual currency = computer cryptography + distributed P2P network + economics + sociology.</p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p>30. Q: what is a third-party wallet?</p><p><br/></p><p>A: it is paid through third-party intervention (only payment platform, not storage data), such as the usual IMTOKEN wallet.</p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p>31. Q: what are the main applications of blockchain?</p><p><br/></p><p>A: digital currency, pan-financial application (cross-border payment, digital bill, credit management, asset securitization, supply chain finance, insurance business), block chain + industry application (block chain + medical treatment, block chain + Internet of things, block chain + IP copyright &amp; cultural entertainment, block chain + public service &amp; education).</p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p>32. Q: what is a trade right?</p><p><br/></p><p>A: a trading pair is made up of two different digital currencies. When you have one of the two digital currencies, you can trade the other through this pair.</p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p>33.Q: what is market value trading?</p><p><br/></p><p>A: do not set namely buy/sell a price, can assure in time clinch a deal, need input to want to buy only total amount can. Market price trading is when you buy at whatever price is in the market right now. It&#39;s called market price buying.</p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p>34.Q: what is a limit transaction?</p><p><br/></p><p>A: limit price trades to hang sheet to trade namely, you can set by yourself buy price, wait for market price fluctuation to be able to clinch a deal when the price that you set. Let&#39;s say you want to buy 1 bitcoin, and you see that the current quotation is 10,000 yuan, and you feel a little bit high at this time, and you want to buy it at 9,900 yuan, you can directly hang a purchase order of 9,900 yuan, and if someone sells it at this price, then your purchase order is successfully traded. That&#39;s when you get a bitcoin into your account.</p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p>35.Q: what are the common currencies?</p><p><br/></p><p>A: a common currency: BTC (COINS) ETH fang (ether) XRP (Rayleigh wave currency) BCH (bits) cash LTC (Wright coin) ADA IDA (currency) XLM stars (c) the NEO (small ant) XMR (Monroe currency) DASH (up to the world currency) ETC (Ethernet) classic USDT COINS (teda) QTUM chains (quantum) EOS (grapefruit) TRX (wave) BNB (COINS COINS) ZEC (big coin).</p><p><br/></p>',0,1567440000,1652637860,'/images/zwtp.png','/images/zwtp.png',0),(89,21,'en','About TCEHK',0,0,0,0,'管理员',0,'About Us','About TCEHK','<p style=\"outline: 0px; text-size-adjust: none; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><span style=\"outline: 0px; text-size-adjust: none; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 14px;\"></span></p><p style=\"outline: 0px; text-size-adjust: none; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><span style=\"outline: 0px; text-size-adjust: none; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 14px;\">TCEHK comes from Japan and aims to provide complete financial services for foreign exchange, stock index, gold, financial currency and cryptocurrency. We are committed to providing safe, convenient and diversified services to meet all cryptocurrency needs, including purchase transactions, pledges, loans, etc.</span><br/></p><p style=\"outline: 0px; text-size-adjust: none; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><br/></p><p style=\"outline: 0px; text-size-adjust: none; -